text: Thymus marschallianus Will . and Thymus proximus Serg . oils from China had lower capacity for preventing lecithin peroxidation than BHT , using TBARS method . Nevertheless , between the oils , that isolated from Thymus proximus had much higher activity . p - Cymene , γ - terpinene and thymol predominated in this ois , whereas in the other oil , only γ - terpinene and thymol dominated . According to these results , the authors [ 54 ] stressed the importance of p - cyme in the antioxidant activity of Thymus proximus , besides thymol and γ - terpinene .
